- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing techniques to detect aggression and loss in social media.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing interactions between users on social media.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using audio data in addition to text data for analysis.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with detecting potential real-world violence based on online behavior.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with social issues related to gang violence and social media.
